  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "There is a bug in the downloader module: a malicious peer could claim a wrong future TD value.\r\nThen the connected nodes would always try to sync with it, since `peerWithHighestTD()` would return the malicious peer.\r\nAnd of course the sync attempt will fail to get the future block, and download procedure will be stuck.\r\n\r\nFor more detail, you may refer: https://forum.bnbchain.org/t/about-recent-feb-2023-node-sync-issue-sidechain-written-to-disk/759\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
